content: Plasma Sky is a very good game. The game has a fun retro space shooter style. There aren't ads or in-game purchases. The gameplay is very fun. There are lots of levels and bosses. Even though there are many similar levels, it doesn't feel repetitive. There are a few different gamemodes, and they're all fun. The Conquest mode, which is the standard mode, is probably the best one. The game doesn't really fit the screen perfectly, but the game is dark so it's not noticeable. In general, it's great!

Great, simple shooter with nice neon graphics. The best part, BY FAR is the controls! Gamepads are supported, which is unique since this is a portrait-oriented game. Also, the touch controls have momentum, meaning if you swipe and let go, your ship keeps its momentum just like a touchpad on a Mac. Finally it has tilt controls that are very precise and snappy! You actually could play this game with tilt controls unlike most others. Awesome game overall!

The graphics are like Tron in space. Has actual powerups instead of unlockable upgrades. Uses a portrait orientation (a must for a phone). Very catchy music. That moment when your ship has seeking spreadshot with three spiked shielded ships shooting laser beams is uh, y'know, like really fun 'n stuff.

I'm not normally into little arcade shooters like this, but I've been looking for something that I could get in and out of quickly when I've got a few moments to spare. Right off the bat, I could tell that the developer had invested a lot of time polishing this little game. Everything from the cool music, to the design of the different ships, this game is something that the dev should be proud of. Many games come and go from my device, but this is the only one that has a permanent spot. Also, I was extremely surprised to see that Moga support had been added to the game recently. The first time I tried playing it with my Moga, I got TWICE as far in the game as I had while previously using touch controls! This game is seriously awesome. Whoever you are developer, I wish I could shake your hand and thank you in person for this.

I was looking for a good arcade style shooter when I came across plasma sky.  Looked good, well reviewed, so I gave it a shot.  Overall I'd say the game is fun, but sparse in some areas and downright flawed in others.  The powerups are quite basic and your primary weapon only has a single upgrade path.  What sours the game for me is that all upgrades, even for your main gun, are temporary.  The game allows you to recoup powerups rapidly at times to catch up, but it also takes away most any sense of strategy

You can even miss them all entirely and still end up with the same score. Makes sense...
replyContent:
Thanks for the review Nicole, glad you're into the game enough to care about your high score!

Did you notice the score multiplier at the top of the screen? It goes up over time, but resets when you get hit. Not getting hit for long stretches can make a HUGE difference, and that may be the variance you're seeing. :)

A very simple, yet elegant power up system matches the simple yet addicting game design.
